name: Young Fish Survey Data 1981 to 2010
description: Total numbers of individual fish identified during the CefasYoung Fish Survey (YFS) which ran from 1981 to 2010. The survey deployed a light 2-meter beam trawl to survey inshore locations for small / young fish around theBritish Isles, predominantly along the southand east coasts. Total numbers of fish (identified to species or if not to thehighesttaxonomic level) were recorded at each station,and were measuredin the majority of cases. The surveys were primarily undertaken to evaluate theabundance of juvenile sole and plaice, as well as providing further information on the abundance of other species of fish. The YFS formed part of the InternationalYoung Fish Survey, coordinated by ICES.
